1
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:35,020
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:37,910
[Episode 7]

3
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,440
It's almost ready, Zongbao.

4
00:01:43,539 --> 00:01:44,560
Dish it up.

5
00:01:44,930 --> 00:01:46,250
Dish up what?

6
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:47,509
Making sauce

7
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:49,259
takes patience.

8
00:01:49,289 --> 00:01:50,620
It smells good enough.

9
00:01:50,620 --> 00:01:51,950
I can't wait any longer.

10
00:01:54,350 --> 00:01:55,550
Ranran, you're back.

11
00:01:57,340 --> 00:01:58,470
Why are you so happy?

12
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:00,060
Look at that smile.

13
00:02:00,310 --> 00:02:01,590
Something good must have happened.

14
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:02,130
Yes.

15
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:04,060
I'm going to meet a director soon.

16
00:02:05,650 --> 00:02:07,060
That's great news.

17
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:08,190
Don't get too excited.

18
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:09,680
It's just the first step.

19
00:02:09,740 --> 00:02:11,270
I need to make it a solid one.

20
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,370
That's the right attitude.

21
00:02:13,370 --> 00:02:14,870
I wouldn't get excited for anyone else.

22
00:02:14,870 --> 00:02:16,920
But for you, I'm thrilled.

23
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:17,980
Look at you.

24
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:20,010
Ranran has improved.

25
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:21,360
She certainly has.

26
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,360
Her Mandarin

27
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,710
is getting better and better.

28
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:25,240
With you guys backing me,

29
00:02:25,340 --> 00:02:26,750
it's hard not to improve.

30
00:02:28,060 --> 00:02:29,060
What are we eating today?

31
00:02:29,060 --> 00:02:29,810
Noodles with fried bean sauce.

32
00:02:29,810 --> 00:02:30,690
Is there any for me?

33
00:02:30,690 --> 00:02:31,800
-Yes.
-Yes.

34
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:32,340
Great.

35
00:02:32,470 --> 00:02:33,000
Ranran.

36
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,520
Let me tell you.

37
00:02:35,020 --> 00:02:36,180
When meeting a director,

38
00:02:36,180 --> 00:02:37,570
you should bring a gift.

39
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:39,410
One can never be too courteous.

40
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,630
I was just about to mention that.

41
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:42,590
I heard that the director

42
00:02:42,590 --> 00:02:43,520
loves drinking.

43
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:45,400
But I know nothing about liquor.

44
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,810
What liquor should I buy?

45
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:48,160
Fenjiu, definitely.

46
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:48,940
From Shanxi.

47
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:49,690
Fenjiu?

48
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,910
If you must bring something, bring the best.

49
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:52,590
Maotai.

50
00:02:52,690 --> 00:02:53,170
Maotai.

51
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,380
Maotai is good.

52
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:56,280
M-Maotai?

53
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,460
How much is Maotai?

54
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:58,560
Probably...

55
00:02:58,780 --> 00:03:00,300
One or two hundred a bottle.

56
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:01,500
That's so expensive.

57
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,740
Forget it. For art.

58
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,660
I'll buy it.

59
00:03:05,970 --> 00:03:06,520
But...

60
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,660
When are you seeing the director?

61
00:03:08,870 --> 00:03:09,470
Tomorrow.

62
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:11,240
It's too late then.

63
00:03:11,810 --> 00:03:13,410
The shops are all closed now.

64
00:03:13,740 --> 00:03:14,130
Ranran,

65
00:03:14,130 --> 00:03:16,329
you want to buy Maotai for the director?

66
00:03:17,210 --> 00:03:18,500
Do you have a connection?

67
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:20,360
I don't have a connection, but...

68
00:03:20,650 --> 00:03:21,579
I have 2 bottles.

69
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,470
Stop bragging.

70
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,750
-You have 2 bottles?
-Hold these for me.

71
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:25,400
Do you have 2 bottles of liquor,

72
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,730
or just 2 empty bottles?

73
00:03:27,410 --> 00:03:28,470
He doesn't even drink.

74
00:03:28,470 --> 00:03:29,870
Why would he have Maotai?

75
00:03:32,210 --> 00:03:33,410
What are these, then?

76
00:03:35,060 --> 00:03:35,460
What are these?

77
00:03:35,460 --> 00:03:35,860
You really have them?

78
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:36,780
You really do.

79
00:03:36,930 --> 00:03:38,030
I was saving them

80
00:03:38,079 --> 00:03:39,650
to give them to the director, too.

81
00:03:39,650 --> 00:03:40,970
But you're seeing him tomorrow.

82
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:42,230
So you take them first.

83
00:03:42,310 --> 00:03:42,800
Right.

84
00:03:43,090 --> 00:03:44,060
With your tolerance,

85
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:46,180
no one would believe they're yours anyway.

86
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:47,690
Such expensive liquors...

87
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:49,190
And you're just giving them away?

88
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:50,180
I'm lending them to her.

89
00:03:50,180 --> 00:03:51,840
If you're going to give a gift,

90
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,560
then...

91
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,090
You have to make it count.

92
00:03:54,130 --> 00:03:55,460
You can't skimp on this.

93
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,050
Mr. Xu,

94
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,180
thank you.

95
00:03:58,780 --> 00:03:59,560
When I get paid,

96
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,900
I'll pay you back immediately.

97
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:01,500
It's fine.

98
00:04:01,870 --> 00:04:03,430
I'll put in a good word with Zhuang Zhuang

99
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:04,190
for you.

100
00:04:05,210 --> 00:04:06,080
No need.

101
00:04:06,530 --> 00:04:06,990
Ranran.

102
00:04:07,210 --> 00:04:08,500
If this works out,

103
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:09,530
what do you want to eat?

104
00:04:09,530 --> 00:04:10,530
I'll make it for you.

105
00:04:10,530 --> 00:04:12,410
These noodles with fried bean sauce
smell great.

106
00:04:12,410 --> 00:04:14,090
Zongbao just finished cooking them
with my guidance.

107
00:04:14,090 --> 00:04:14,620
Let's go.

108
00:04:14,740 --> 00:04:15,780
Let's set up the table.

109
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:16,779
Let's go, Ranran.

110
00:04:16,950 --> 00:04:18,860
With your guidance?

111
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:20,390
I simmered it for 20 minutes.

112
00:04:20,390 --> 00:04:21,320
What a braggart.

113
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:23,750
Zongbao.

114
00:04:24,330 --> 00:04:26,240
Add less sugar next time.

115
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:29,850
Let's not go inside.

116
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:31,840
The 3 of us will eat here.

117
00:04:32,310 --> 00:04:32,770
Okay.

118
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:34,659
I'll get the noodles for you.

119
00:04:37,890 --> 00:04:38,350
Zhuang.

120
00:04:38,740 --> 00:04:39,980
No, my loyal subject.

121
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:43,000
I grant you ten thousand taels of gold

122
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,450
and several fine horses.

123
00:04:46,010 --> 00:04:47,270
You're unbelievable.

124
00:04:47,930 --> 00:04:48,390
Zhuang.

125
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,610
Come here, quickly.

126
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:51,100
Look at me.

127
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,240
Who do I look like?

128
00:04:53,250 --> 00:04:54,159
Wu Zetian?

129
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:56,550
Zhuang, how did you guess it?

130
00:04:56,810 --> 00:04:58,210
Your acting was on point.

131
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,690
-Have you chosen the clothes?
-Of course.

132
00:04:59,690 --> 00:05:00,740
I think every piece

133
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:01,470
looks great.

134
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,280
Every piece looks beautiful

135
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:04,930
on me.

136
00:05:06,420 --> 00:05:07,280
Servant,

137
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:09,670
pass down my command immediately.

138
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:12,300
Serve the Imperial Feast.

139
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:15,570
Here.

140
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,860
Alright, Your Highness. Time to change.

141
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:20,950
Look at you, so happy.

142
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:22,630
Zhuang.

143
00:05:23,310 --> 00:05:24,510
Right now,

144
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,560
I feel so happy.

145
00:05:27,190 --> 00:05:28,070
Be careful.

146
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:30,030
It's good to be happy.

147
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:31,040
From now on, happy things

148
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,170
will only increase.

149
00:05:33,370 --> 00:05:33,860
Look.

150
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:37,300
Which one do you think looks better?

151
00:05:37,630 --> 00:05:38,500
The yellow one.

152
00:05:38,770 --> 00:05:41,060
It matches your hair accessory perfectly.

153
00:05:41,060 --> 00:05:42,070
I think so too.

154
00:05:42,130 --> 00:05:43,659
I'll listen to you, Zhuang.

155
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,260
Come on.

156
00:05:52,510 --> 00:05:54,190
Wait a second. I'm almost done.

157
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:55,320
Working hard, I see.

158
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:09,660
I heard that you did someone

159
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:11,190
a favor again today, Mr. Xu.

160
00:06:13,220 --> 00:06:15,190
Meeting the director is a big deal.

161
00:06:15,540 --> 00:06:16,570
I really hope that

162
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:17,700
Ranran can succeed.

163
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:19,200
You empathize with her.

164
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,000
Something like that.

165
00:06:25,450 --> 00:06:27,510
Director Weng will be back soon, too.

166
00:06:31,180 --> 00:06:32,650
I had a fight with him.

167
00:06:32,770 --> 00:06:34,560
Do you think it'll affect things?

168
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,480
After a hurricane comes the rainbow.

169
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,340
Don't you know?

170
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,550
Yes.

171
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:43,540
After a hurricane comes the rainbow.

172
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:48,670
The simplest kind of support

173
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,530
seems to be the most useful.

174
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:55,480
Yeah.

175
00:06:56,510 --> 00:06:58,690
The simplest support works best.

176
00:06:59,630 --> 00:07:01,430
Earning money with you

177
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:02,620
for the long haul

178
00:07:02,980 --> 00:07:04,110
is pretty good, too.

179
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,300
Hurry up and write.

180
00:07:13,570 --> 00:07:14,540
I just finished a section.

181
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:15,940
Why don't you take a look?

182
00:07:16,620 --> 00:07:18,510
Will I even understand your script?

183
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:19,630
What's there not to understand?

184
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:20,600
It's just a story.

185
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,260
Take a look.

186
00:07:21,980 --> 00:07:22,590
Alright.

187
00:07:25,980 --> 00:07:27,040
Nice handwriting.

188
00:07:27,130 --> 00:07:27,890
What does that mean?

189
00:07:27,890 --> 00:07:29,130
Is the content not good?

190
00:07:29,130 --> 00:07:29,810
Be quiet.

191
00:07:44,670 --> 00:07:46,790
[Welcome "Outsider" Crew To Our Hotel]

192
00:07:47,620 --> 00:07:50,480
["Outsider" Production Team]

193
00:07:50,510 --> 00:07:53,980
[Director's Studio]

194
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:52,740
Coming.

195
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:55,159
You're here.

196
00:07:55,159 --> 00:07:56,000
Quick, come in.

197
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:56,420
Okay.

198
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:57,360
Come on.

199
00:07:57,220 --> 00:08:01,590
[Prop cars] [Prop IDs]

200
00:07:58,390 --> 00:07:59,120
Director Ma.

201
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,930
This is the person I mentioned to you,

202
00:08:00,930 --> 00:08:01,660
Shen Ranran.

203
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,430
Director!

204
00:08:03,540 --> 00:08:04,190
Director!

205
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,690
Your hands are made for directing.

206
00:08:04,970 --> 00:08:10,050
[Character settings]

207
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:06,420
Let me do it.

208
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:07,550
Please, have a seat.

209
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,600
Director, well.

210
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:11,920
Ranran is from Huzhou.

211
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:13,410
Her acting is pretty good.

212
00:08:14,580 --> 00:08:16,060
Just because you say so?

213
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,280
Director.

214
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:19,530
I talk too much.

215
00:08:19,660 --> 00:08:20,590
You be the judge.

216
00:08:22,510 --> 00:08:23,240
Director Ma.

217
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,750
Mr. Cui asked me to come here.

218
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:25,870
It's my first time meeting you.

219
00:08:25,870 --> 00:08:27,240
I didn't know what to bring.

220
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:29,000
I just bought 2 bottles of good liquor

221
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,800
for you to try.

222
00:08:29,810 --> 00:08:31,070
Please look out for me.

223
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,940
That's so thoughtful.

224
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:34,370
Well...

225
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,630
Director.

226
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:38,080
Wine and meat just pass through us.

227
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:38,940
It's harmless.

228
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,150
This liquor makes our food

229
00:08:42,150 --> 00:08:42,960
look lacking.

230
00:08:43,370 --> 00:08:45,150
Shall I go buy a few more dishes?

231
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:46,970
Why are you asking?

232
00:08:46,980 --> 00:08:47,910
I'll go with you.

233
00:08:48,060 --> 00:08:49,520
[Character settings]

234
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,530
Let me tell you, Ranran.

235
00:08:54,650 --> 00:08:55,850
These 4 dishes

236
00:08:55,980 --> 00:08:57,840
have been blessed by Director Ma's aura.

237
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,670
Even the finest delicacies can't compare.

238
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:00,630
You and your mouth.

239
00:09:00,630 --> 00:09:02,720
Keep talking, and the food will get cold.

240
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,720
Come, have a seat.

241
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:05,390
Thank you, Director Ma.

242
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:14,750
[Character settings]

243
00:09:06,290 --> 00:09:06,720
Director.

244
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:07,920
I'll use the teacups.

245
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:08,340
Okay.

246
00:09:09,820 --> 00:09:10,130
Here.

247
00:09:10,130 --> 00:09:11,460
Thank you, Director Ma.

248
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:13,650
Let me do it.

249
00:09:13,670 --> 00:09:14,670
Let me, Director.

250
00:09:17,980 --> 00:09:18,710
Director Ma,

251
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,020
have a look.

252
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,450
You shouldn't have.

253
00:09:37,030 --> 00:09:37,460
Director.

254
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:38,630
Let me pour it.

255
00:09:38,770 --> 00:09:39,440
Here.

256
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:40,370
Okay.

257
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:47,010
Here.

258
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:54,150
Thank you, Mr. Cui.

259
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:54,600
Here.

260
00:10:00,550 --> 00:10:01,280
Director Ma.

261
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,840
Ranran and I would like to offer you a toast.

262
00:10:05,530 --> 00:10:06,240
Okay.

263
00:10:06,630 --> 00:10:08,560
Wish you good health, Director Ma.

264
00:10:08,620 --> 00:10:09,500
May you create more great titles

265
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:10,630
and win more awards.

266
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:12,660
Thank you.

267
00:10:13,170 --> 00:10:13,890
She has a way with words.

268
00:10:13,790 --> 00:10:16,060
[Prop IDs]

269
00:10:13,890 --> 00:10:15,090
Even better than you.

270
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:32,740
Young lady,

271
00:10:33,980 --> 00:10:35,970
I noticed when you drank just now,

272
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:38,200
you frowned a little.

273
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:39,760
What's wrong?

274
00:10:40,250 --> 00:10:40,720
I...

275
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:43,180
I've never had this liquor before.

276
00:10:43,370 --> 00:10:44,430
It's quite strong.

277
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:51,780
Good liquor

278
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:53,910
is always strong.

279
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,420
It's getting cold.

280
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:58,980
Come on, eat up.

281
00:10:59,150 --> 00:10:59,580
Have some food.

282
00:10:59,580 --> 00:10:59,940
Okay.

283
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,340
It's all getting cold.

284
00:11:02,220 --> 00:11:03,950
Come on. Make yourself at home.

285
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,080
Come on.

286
00:11:08,090 --> 00:11:11,830
[Welcome "Outsider" Crew To Our Hotel]

287
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:08,890
Mr. Cui.

288
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,050
Mr. Cui.

289
00:11:10,550 --> 00:11:11,770
Mr. Cui.

290
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:14,140
Isn't Director Ma a big drinker?

291
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:15,870
Why did he only drink 1 cup?

292
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:17,930
Did he not like the liquor?

293
00:11:18,050 --> 00:11:19,780
Or was it too precious to drink?

294
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,510
Probably too precious.

295
00:11:22,510 --> 00:11:22,960
So,

296
00:11:23,970 --> 00:11:25,590
what does he think of me?

297
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:26,790
What do you think?

298
00:11:26,910 --> 00:11:28,080
I don't know.

299
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,130
During the meal,

300
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:30,260
he didn't say a word.

301
00:11:30,580 --> 00:11:31,740
I didn't dare to ask.

302
00:11:32,170 --> 00:11:32,750
I know.

303
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,370
You're done for.

304
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,040
Don't you get it, Ranran?

305
00:11:40,370 --> 00:11:41,820
The liquor you brought was blended.

306
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:43,040
It wasn't authentic.

307
00:11:43,170 --> 00:11:44,170
That's impossible.

308
00:11:44,170 --> 00:11:45,150
Why is it impossible?

309
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:46,200
Director Ma is a connoisseur.

310
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,010
He's had every kind of liquor.

311
00:11:47,010 --> 00:11:48,600
Even I could taste that it was fake.

312
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,080
But Director Ma drank a cup.

313
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,280
He didn't spit it out.

314
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,960
You expect him to spit it out?

315
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:55,740
Why are you so naive?

316
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:56,750
I told you,

317
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:57,820
he is a director.

318
00:11:58,550 --> 00:12:00,010
He was being considerate.

319
00:12:01,150 --> 00:12:02,200
Anyway,

320
00:12:02,870 --> 00:12:04,270
it's probably hopeless.

321
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,120
That bottle cap had been opened.

322
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:12,740
Most likely,

323
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:14,990
they definitely gave you fake liquor.

324
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:15,790
Impossible.

325
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:16,940
They aren't like that.

326
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:18,390
Who isn't like that?

327
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:20,580
You're too naive, Ranran.

328
00:12:21,010 --> 00:12:21,360
I...

329
00:12:22,530 --> 00:12:23,170
Do you remember what Director Ma

330
00:12:23,170 --> 00:12:24,000
said to you?

331
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,000
He told you to manage

332
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,290
your interpersonal relationships.

333
00:12:26,290 --> 00:12:27,550
That was a warning.

334
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,120
This... Then...

335
00:12:30,630 --> 00:12:31,230
Then...

336
00:12:31,460 --> 00:12:32,350
Then this time,

337
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,120
do I have no chance?

338
00:12:35,460 --> 00:12:35,940
Well...

339
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,010
Don't cry.

340
00:12:38,390 --> 00:12:39,640
Listen,

341
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:41,400
the role hasn't been cast yet.

342
00:12:41,530 --> 00:12:43,660
So there might still be a spark of hope.

343
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,720
No, I can't be left with just a spark.

344
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:46,670
You have to help me.

345
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:48,320
We need to stoke the fire.

346
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:48,940
How?

347
00:12:49,170 --> 00:12:50,430
Pour fake liquor on it?

348
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:53,770
This...

349
00:12:54,010 --> 00:12:55,870
What am I supposed to do?

350
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:57,980
I must find

351
00:12:57,980 --> 00:12:59,120
the culprit

352
00:12:59,940 --> 00:13:01,120
and clear my name.

353
00:13:06,270 --> 00:13:07,400
Where is Xu Shengli?

354
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:08,750
Not here.

355
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,340
What's wrong, Ranran?

356
00:13:12,410 --> 00:13:13,740
It smells like alcohol.

357
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:16,600
None of you are getting away with this.

358
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,400
What alcohol?

359
00:13:17,460 --> 00:13:18,390
Open your mouth.

360
00:13:19,220 --> 00:13:19,670
What do you mean?

361
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:20,600
Open your mouth.

362
00:13:23,790 --> 00:13:24,840
I just ate garlic.

363
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,430
Six cloves of it.

364
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:27,510
You open up, too.

365
00:13:28,460 --> 00:13:28,860
Me?

366
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:33,890
Come on.

367
00:13:33,890 --> 00:13:35,690
I... I just had some chili sauce.

368
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:37,270
I...

369
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:40,530
I just had stinky tofu.

370
00:13:42,510 --> 00:13:43,770
What's wrong, Ranran?

371
00:13:44,460 --> 00:13:46,390
Take your time and speak your mind.

372
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:49,050
How did it go with Director Ma?

373
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,100
The 2 bottles of liquor you gave me

374
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:54,060
were fake.

375
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,120
-What?
-What?

376
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:55,700
What's going on?

377
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:56,630
What? What liquor?

378
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:57,050
What liquor?

379
00:13:57,050 --> 00:13:58,480
The 2 bottles Xu Shengli gave me

380
00:13:58,480 --> 00:13:59,580
were fake!

381
00:14:00,050 --> 00:14:01,580
I've offended the director

382
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:02,860
and lost my chance at acting.

383
00:14:02,860 --> 00:14:03,440
My life has been ruined

384
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:05,300
by those 2 bottles of fake liquor!

385
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,010
I shouldn't have

386
00:14:06,010 --> 00:14:07,720
given those 2 bottles of liquor.

387
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,700
Why are you trying to ruin it for me?

388
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:12,800
You've completely ruined it!

389
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:15,700
It's over.

390
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,820
It's all over now.

391
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:19,790
I offended the director.

392
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:22,150
I'll never get another role.

393
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,630
It can't be that bad.

394
00:14:24,820 --> 00:14:26,670
Forget it.

395
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:29,760
No matter how nice my words were,

396
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:31,720
I ended up giving fake liquor

397
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,650
to the director.

398
00:14:32,870 --> 00:14:34,630
He... he must think

399
00:14:34,630 --> 00:14:36,240
I did it on purpose.

400
00:14:36,290 --> 00:14:38,000
You can't be blamed for this.

401
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,920
Just explain it to the director.

402
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:45,710
Did Xu Shengli

403
00:14:46,410 --> 00:14:47,580
do it on purpose?

404
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:50,860
He's definitely not that kind of person.

405
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:53,320
Zhuang,

406
00:14:54,270 --> 00:14:56,200
you're siding with him.

407
00:14:57,510 --> 00:14:58,240
Don't worry.

408
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:01,000
I will definitely find the culprit for you.

409
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:02,700
Zhuang Zhuang.

410
00:15:02,790 --> 00:15:04,130
Open the door.

411
00:15:04,370 --> 00:15:06,150
Ranran is still crying over there.

412
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,370
She's crying her heart out.

413
00:15:07,370 --> 00:15:08,890
I feel terrible, too.

414
00:15:08,890 --> 00:15:10,550
Let me go over and comfort her.

415
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:12,360
Zhuang Zhuang!

416
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,200
Then help Mr. Guo out.

417
00:15:15,740 --> 00:15:17,120
He's getting on in years.

418
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,270
He has prostate issues.

419
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:19,860
He needs to use the bathroom.

420
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:20,940
What are you doing?

421
00:15:20,940 --> 00:15:21,270
No...

422
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,670
He can't hold it in anymore.

423
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:26,150
Zhuang Zhuang.

424
00:15:26,940 --> 00:15:29,250
I can't hold it in anymore.

425
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,690
Open the door, quickly.

426
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:34,470
Zhuang Zhuang, I can't hold it anymore.

427
00:15:34,940 --> 00:15:36,710
What should I do?

428
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:39,650
Should I pee in this bottle?

429
00:15:40,630 --> 00:15:41,670
It's too small.

430
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:44,510
How about this one?

431
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:45,370
Make do with it.

432
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:47,150
You're crazy, Tao Liangliang.

433
00:15:47,150 --> 00:15:47,670
This works.

434
00:15:47,670 --> 00:15:48,600
This won't work.

435
00:15:48,620 --> 00:15:49,550
This is great.

436
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:50,150
Open the door, quickly.

437
00:15:50,150 --> 00:15:50,840
Wait a minute, Zongbao.

438
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:51,940
I'll find you something even

439
00:15:51,940 --> 00:15:52,980
more exciting.

440
00:15:54,030 --> 00:15:55,720
No, that's no good. No good.

441
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:56,410
That won't do.

442
00:15:56,410 --> 00:15:57,460
What's wrong? Yours won't do,

443
00:15:57,460 --> 00:15:58,050
but mine is ok?

444
00:15:58,050 --> 00:15:58,550
No.

445
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:00,580
This isn't exciting. Not exciting.

446
00:16:00,580 --> 00:16:02,200
It is. It's really exciting.

447
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,180
Don't block me.

448
00:16:05,170 --> 00:16:06,050
Zhuang Zhuang.

449
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:07,240
Open the door.

450
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:08,800
I can't hold it in anymore.

451
00:16:08,820 --> 00:16:09,840
I'm dying here.

452
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:11,290
Hurry up and open the door.

453
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:13,220
Alright, stop shouting. It's useless.

454
00:16:13,220 --> 00:16:15,200
Useless or not, we can't just wait here.

455
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,790
Why are you just standing here?

456
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:17,990
I was waiting for you.

457
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:18,800
What's wrong?

458
00:16:19,130 --> 00:16:20,460
It's about Shen Ranran.

459
00:16:21,170 --> 00:16:22,120
I told her

460
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,850
there's no need to be so polite.

461
00:16:25,370 --> 00:16:26,380
I bought some food

462
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,460
to thank everyone for their care.

463
00:16:28,620 --> 00:16:29,680
We'll eat and talk.

464
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:30,680
Let's go inside.

465
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:43,920
Oh, everyone's here.

466
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:46,460
Zhuang Zhuang brought us some food.

467
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,560
You finally opened the door.

468
00:16:52,130 --> 00:16:53,500
What are you doing?

469
00:16:54,130 --> 00:16:55,930
Give me a straight answer today.

470
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:58,170
What happened to Ranran's liquor?

471
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:10,430
Not talking?

472
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:12,050
Fine.

473
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,240
Then I'll torture you one by one.

474
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:15,300
Starting with you.

475
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:16,140
No, wait.

476
00:17:16,849 --> 00:17:17,310
What...

477
00:17:17,569 --> 00:17:18,970
What exactly is going on?

478
00:17:20,510 --> 00:17:22,710
The liquor you gave Shen Ranran is fake.

479
00:17:25,109 --> 00:17:25,980
Fake liquor?

480
00:17:27,569 --> 00:17:28,720
That's impossible.

481
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,180
I bought it at the state-run store.

482
00:17:30,180 --> 00:17:31,240
I have the receipt.

483
00:17:39,710 --> 00:17:41,400
[Receipt]

484
00:17:46,450 --> 00:17:48,050
Could it have been switched?

485
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:49,840
That's even less likely.

486
00:17:50,090 --> 00:17:51,240
The liquor was under my bed the whole time.

487
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,300
I never took it out.

488
00:17:56,810 --> 00:17:58,000
Then the suspect must be

489
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:58,800
from Room 108.

490
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:04,450
What's going on?

491
00:18:07,530 --> 00:18:08,260
You go first.

492
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:13,060
Then you should rule me out first.

493
00:18:13,830 --> 00:18:15,890
I bought the liquor for the director.

494
00:18:16,010 --> 00:18:17,330
So I'm a victim too.

495
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:17,920
Right?

496
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:20,040
Listen, Xu.

497
00:18:21,510 --> 00:18:23,380
You're just passing the buck

498
00:18:25,330 --> 00:18:26,990
and keeping your hands clean.

499
00:18:27,610 --> 00:18:28,590
Exactly.

500
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,940
You share the weals but not the woes.

501
00:18:30,940 --> 00:18:31,880
How could you?

502
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:34,000
What are you doing?

503
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,650
We're all from the same room.

504
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:38,070
At night, we all hear

505
00:18:38,510 --> 00:18:39,370
each other burp

506
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:40,530
and grind our teeth.

507
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:42,750
We even hear each other's sleep-talking.

508
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,250
We keep an eye on each other, right?

509
00:18:44,250 --> 00:18:46,250
There are no bad people in this room.

510
00:18:47,950 --> 00:18:49,150
Your arm is on my hair.

511
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:53,740
Who exactly did it?

512
00:18:54,010 --> 00:18:55,410
If it pertains to Ranran,

513
00:18:55,480 --> 00:18:57,680
it definitely couldn't have been me, right?

514
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:58,830
It wasn't me either.

515
00:19:02,010 --> 00:19:03,410
Process of elimination?

516
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:04,720
The one who walked in

517
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:06,120
ruled himself out first.

518
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:07,290
You said it pertained to Ranran,

519
00:19:07,290 --> 00:19:08,350
so it couldn't have been you,

520
00:19:08,350 --> 00:19:09,640
and absolutely not you.

521
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:10,640
So that leaves me.

522
00:19:10,980 --> 00:19:11,330
Fine.

523
00:19:12,290 --> 00:19:13,750
You actually admitted it.

524
00:19:14,510 --> 00:19:15,940
Admit what?

525
00:19:15,940 --> 00:19:17,740
I was just joking.

526
00:19:17,790 --> 00:19:19,220
It's a good thing you aren't judges.

527
00:19:19,220 --> 00:19:20,070
Otherwise, so many people

528
00:19:20,070 --> 00:19:21,380
would have been wrongly executed.

529
00:19:21,380 --> 00:19:23,110
Bring out the guillotine.

530
00:19:23,380 --> 00:19:24,220
Exactly.

531
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,660
Now you're joking around?

532
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:34,900
No, we're not.

533
00:19:35,660 --> 00:19:36,570
Do you know how important

534
00:19:36,570 --> 00:19:37,990
this is to her?

535
00:19:38,440 --> 00:19:39,900
I'm telling you right now.

536
00:19:40,140 --> 00:19:41,830
Until we get to the bottom of this,

537
00:19:41,830 --> 00:19:43,360
no one is leaving this room.

538
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:44,660
Think it over.

539
00:19:45,310 --> 00:19:47,110
It'll be too late once the police get here.

540
00:19:47,110 --> 00:19:47,570
Fine.

541
00:19:48,940 --> 00:19:50,560
Let's cut the crap.

542
00:19:50,610 --> 00:19:51,540
Call the police.

543
00:19:51,940 --> 00:19:52,880
Call them right now.

544
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:53,440
No, no.

545
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:53,940
Zongbao.

546
00:19:53,940 --> 00:19:56,470
No, no. The police will investigate me first.

547
00:19:56,740 --> 00:19:57,870
Investigate, then.

548
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:59,360
We must investigate this.

549
00:19:59,570 --> 00:20:00,500
Call the police.

550
00:20:01,330 --> 00:20:03,210
We'll get to the bottom of this

551
00:20:03,380 --> 00:20:04,750
so I can beat the culprit up.

552
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:06,280
We'll find out who did it...

553
00:20:07,270 --> 00:20:08,800
And teach him a good lesson.

554
00:20:08,810 --> 00:20:09,270
You...

555
00:20:09,270 --> 00:20:09,720
Investigate it!

556
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:10,850
Where are you going?

557
00:20:10,940 --> 00:20:11,870
To the bathroom!

558
00:20:13,010 --> 00:20:13,870
Zhuang Zhuang.

559
00:20:14,510 --> 00:20:16,690
Go back and tell Ranran that

560
00:20:17,330 --> 00:20:19,560
she can leave this swapped liquor case

561
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:20,380
to me.

562
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:22,270
I will definitely

563
00:20:22,270 --> 00:20:23,930
get to the bottom of it for her.

564
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:28,280
I'll go take a leak first.

565
00:20:30,750 --> 00:20:31,560
Don't worry.

566
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:34,130
I said I'd help you investigate it,

567
00:20:34,660 --> 00:20:36,990
so I'll definitely get to the bottom of it.

568
00:20:44,390 --> 00:20:46,830
[Guest Room]

569
00:20:50,770 --> 00:20:51,870
Washing up?

570
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:03,760
You already promised her.

571
00:21:03,790 --> 00:21:05,440
How do you plan to investigate?

572
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:06,250
I...

573
00:21:06,830 --> 00:21:08,090
have figured out a way.

574
00:21:10,570 --> 00:21:12,100
You've figured it out, too?

575
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:16,470
What are you grinning at?

576
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:23,810
Others laugh at me for being too crazy,

577
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:27,680
but I laugh at others
for not seeing through it.

578
00:21:28,610 --> 00:21:31,500
So... You have it in the bag?

579
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:34,520
What are you doing?

580
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:37,560
Do you suspect me?

581
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,660
Have you ever had good liquor?

582
00:21:44,180 --> 00:21:45,380
Actually, I haven't.

583
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:47,370
Then sniffing me is pointless.

584
00:21:48,460 --> 00:21:50,120
Even if it's a shot in the dark,

585
00:21:50,850 --> 00:21:52,580
I can always take a swing first.

586
00:21:52,810 --> 00:21:54,670
You're taking a swing at me first?

587
00:22:58,510 --> 00:22:59,380
What are you doing?

588
00:22:59,380 --> 00:23:00,580
What's going on?

589
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:01,830
What's wrong?

590
00:23:03,380 --> 00:23:05,180
-What’s wrong?
-What happened?

591
00:23:06,530 --> 00:23:08,260
It's spicy!

592
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:10,240
You liquor thief!

593
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:13,010
What thief? Who's a thief?

594
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:14,650
What's going on?

595
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,600
Did you steal the liquor?

596
00:23:16,660 --> 00:23:17,390
What is this?

597
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:20,180
Why is there a tube?

598
00:23:24,050 --> 00:23:25,180
What's this about?

599
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:30,460
Sit down.

600
00:23:33,310 --> 00:23:36,000
Leniency for confession,
severity for resistance.

601
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:36,420
Speak.

602
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:38,200
You stole Xu's liquor,

603
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,000
poured the real liquor into

604
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,400
the bottle you prepared,

605
00:23:42,330 --> 00:23:43,790
and put the adulterated liquor

606
00:23:43,790 --> 00:23:45,520
back into the original bottle.

607
00:23:46,140 --> 00:23:46,870
Heretic Cao.

608
00:23:48,050 --> 00:23:50,540
You should change your name to Wicked Cao.

609
00:23:50,610 --> 00:23:51,000
I

610
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,090
didn't know those 2 bottles

611
00:23:52,090 --> 00:23:54,290
were gifts before I tampered with them.

612
00:23:54,310 --> 00:23:56,050
I certainly didn't know they were for Ranran.

613
00:23:56,050 --> 00:23:56,450
You...

614
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:58,080
The point is, think about it.

615
00:23:58,110 --> 00:23:59,420
With Xu Shengli's alcohol tolerance,

616
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:00,720
isn't it a complete waste

617
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:01,590
of good liquor

618
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:03,610
for him to sleep on 2 bottles

619
00:24:03,770 --> 00:24:04,660
of fine liquor?

620
00:24:04,770 --> 00:24:05,770
If I had known earlier,

621
00:24:05,770 --> 00:24:07,830
I definitely wouldn't have drunk it.

622
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,420
Why are you still making excuses?

623
00:24:09,420 --> 00:24:10,070
Look at you.

624
00:24:10,070 --> 00:24:11,480
You think you're in the right, don't you?

625
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:12,680
Stay seated. You...

626
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:13,590
You...

627
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:17,510
You can steal anything

628
00:24:18,510 --> 00:24:19,290
but liquor.

629
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:20,920
You're at fault.

630
00:24:21,570 --> 00:24:23,220
I am at fault.

631
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:24,880
But...

632
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:26,240
I... I just

633
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,850
hadn't had good liquor before, okay?

634
00:24:27,850 --> 00:24:29,220
Since I saw it,

635
00:24:29,220 --> 00:24:30,820
how could I have resisted it?

636
00:24:31,330 --> 00:24:33,530
Yes, I admit that I've drunk the liquor.

637
00:24:33,850 --> 00:24:35,580
But I can't afford to pay for it.

638
00:24:35,940 --> 00:24:37,270
So... as for Ranran,

639
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:38,880
if all else fails...

640
00:24:40,290 --> 00:24:41,090
My paintings.

641
00:24:41,090 --> 00:24:42,500
Look at all these paintings of mine.

642
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:43,740
-Let Ranran pick one.
-Enough.

643
00:24:43,740 --> 00:24:44,380
If she doesn't like any of them,

644
00:24:44,380 --> 00:24:45,640
I can paint another one for her.

645
00:24:45,640 --> 00:24:47,200
She can give it to that director.

646
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,310
Just tell the director that

647
00:24:48,310 --> 00:24:49,980
when Cao Ye becomes famous overnight,

648
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:53,180
the painting will be worth
more than a bottle of liquor...

649
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:55,980
Wait a minute.

650
00:24:56,460 --> 00:24:58,120
I didn't drink a whole bottle.

651
00:24:58,380 --> 00:25:00,330
I only drank less than half a bottle.

652
00:25:00,330 --> 00:25:01,310
Who swapped the rest

653
00:25:01,310 --> 00:25:02,380
with chili water?

654
00:25:04,310 --> 00:25:05,660
This is a separate matter.

655
00:25:05,660 --> 00:25:07,590
Is that something a human would do?

656
00:25:07,660 --> 00:25:09,500
Don't push your luck after getting off easy.

657
00:25:09,500 --> 00:25:11,000
I have other stuff here. You want some?

658
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,330
That's enough from you.

659
00:25:13,790 --> 00:25:14,290
Xu.

660
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:15,920
Say something.

661
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:26,460
Xu Shengli.

662
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:27,960
Is our feud

663
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:29,010
ever going to end?

664
00:25:29,270 --> 00:25:31,330
I should be the one saying that to you.

665
00:25:35,750 --> 00:25:37,640
Where is the other bottle of liquor?

666
00:25:37,640 --> 00:25:38,480
I swear to God,

667
00:25:38,510 --> 00:25:39,640
I only took 1 bottle.

668
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:42,110
So one bottle is authentic.

669
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:45,540
Yes, one bottle is authentic.

670
00:25:45,570 --> 00:25:46,140
I'm not that kind of

671
00:25:46,140 --> 00:25:46,700
greedy person.

672
00:25:46,700 --> 00:25:47,240
Tomorrow morning,

673
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:49,300
go apologize to Ranran immediately.

674
00:25:49,810 --> 00:25:50,610
I will, I will.

675
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:06,170
We're just missing the liquor.

676
00:26:09,610 --> 00:26:11,470
Let me make my stance clear again.

677
00:26:11,660 --> 00:26:13,250
I will definitely apologize.

678
00:26:13,250 --> 00:26:14,590
But now that the liquor is poured out,

679
00:26:14,590 --> 00:26:15,980
it can't be poured back, can it?

680
00:26:15,980 --> 00:26:18,110
I'll have to pay for it sooner or later.

681
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:20,050
One day, when I become famous,

682
00:26:20,050 --> 00:26:20,810
just one of my paintings

683
00:26:20,810 --> 00:26:22,610
will be worth 10 or 20 cases of it.

684
00:26:24,500 --> 00:26:24,900
I...

685
00:26:25,010 --> 00:26:25,420
I...

686
00:26:29,110 --> 00:26:29,570
This...

687
00:26:33,610 --> 00:26:34,480
This liquor

688
00:26:35,050 --> 00:26:35,910
smells so good.

689
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:37,320
It really does.

690
00:26:37,830 --> 00:26:39,240
Ranran's liquor

691
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:40,900
is for me only.

692
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:43,100
I bought it. Let go.

693
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:47,510
Let go!

694
00:26:49,380 --> 00:26:51,810
1, 2, 3.

695
00:26:54,110 --> 00:26:54,770
Go to sleep.

696
00:26:56,380 --> 00:26:57,960
Can you even sleep?

697
00:27:17,610 --> 00:27:18,380
Come take a look, Miss.

698
00:27:18,380 --> 00:27:19,710
Feel free to take a look.

699
00:27:28,900 --> 00:27:29,530
Ranran.

700
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:33,790
What a small world.

701
00:27:33,900 --> 00:27:35,420
What are you doing here?

702
00:27:37,420 --> 00:27:38,740
Well, it's raining.

703
00:27:38,770 --> 00:27:40,940
I'm looking for inspiration here.

704
00:27:42,590 --> 00:27:43,460
Inspiration?

705
00:27:50,390 --> 00:27:52,770
Do you usually perform here?

706
00:27:55,110 --> 00:27:55,770
Perform...

707
00:27:57,290 --> 00:27:58,110
The performance, yes.

708
00:27:58,110 --> 00:27:59,530
The posters are up.

709
00:28:01,010 --> 00:28:02,340
"Carefree Wandering."

710
00:28:02,770 --> 00:28:04,310
Beijing Song and Dance Troupe.

711
00:28:04,310 --> 00:28:06,380
I'm auditioning for this troupe later.

712
00:28:06,380 --> 00:28:07,160
The main musician's role,

713
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,290
with a solo!

714
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,420
What do you mean by "sour"?

715
00:28:12,500 --> 00:28:14,320
No, not "sour."

716
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:16,110
Solo.

717
00:28:16,370 --> 00:28:16,920
It means,

718
00:28:17,310 --> 00:28:18,380
in the middle of the

719
00:28:18,610 --> 00:28:19,410
performance,

720
00:28:19,500 --> 00:28:21,160
I have a segment all to myself.

721
00:28:21,610 --> 00:28:23,290
All the eyes will be on me.

722
00:28:23,290 --> 00:28:24,270
And all the lights

723
00:28:24,270 --> 00:28:26,290
will gather on me.

724
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:27,960
It's dazzling.

725
00:28:38,810 --> 00:28:39,900
It's raining.

726
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:42,610
You didn't bring an umbrella, did you?

727
00:28:44,660 --> 00:28:45,380
I did.

728
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:46,960
Let's walk together.

729
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:47,740
Wait for me.

730
00:29:06,750 --> 00:29:07,350
Dazzling.

731
00:29:10,850 --> 00:29:11,550
Thanks.

732
00:29:11,590 --> 00:29:12,520
You're welcome.

733
00:29:35,090 --> 00:29:35,620
If you...

734
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:37,850
Have plans...

735
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:38,590
I'm free.

736
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,880
This is nice.

737
00:29:49,070 --> 00:29:50,140
Actually,

738
00:29:50,290 --> 00:29:52,010
I take the bus a lot

739
00:29:52,010 --> 00:29:53,670
to see the scenery in Beijing.

740
00:29:54,090 --> 00:29:55,390
Every time I look,

741
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:57,230
I see a different side of it.

742
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,580
Even though I'm from Beijing,

743
00:30:00,220 --> 00:30:01,440
I rarely

744
00:30:03,350 --> 00:30:04,750
get to know the city

745
00:30:05,140 --> 00:30:05,770
like this.

746
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:12,820
You're actually quite different

747
00:30:13,270 --> 00:30:14,750
from what I imagined.

748
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:16,410
So you've thought about me?

749
00:30:33,050 --> 00:30:34,250
Actually,

750
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:37,050
I'm quite grateful for the rain today.

751
00:30:37,440 --> 00:30:39,770
Otherwise, I wouldn't have had the chance

752
00:30:40,700 --> 00:30:42,030
to let you get to know me.

753
00:30:45,310 --> 00:30:47,740
My family runs a restaurant.

754
00:30:49,010 --> 00:30:50,430
To be precise,

755
00:30:51,920 --> 00:30:53,050
it's a small diner.

756
00:30:54,420 --> 00:30:55,900
Back in high school,

757
00:30:56,380 --> 00:30:57,580
I was always fighting

758
00:30:57,680 --> 00:30:58,880
and causing trouble.

759
00:30:58,980 --> 00:31:00,010
Later, I don't know

760
00:31:00,010 --> 00:31:02,110
what wire in my brain

761
00:31:02,270 --> 00:31:03,000
got crossed,

762
00:31:03,010 --> 00:31:05,340
but I insisted on learning the saxophone.

763
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:09,050
My family didn't agree.

764
00:31:10,110 --> 00:31:10,960
But one night,

765
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,560
my mom went to the city center

766
00:31:13,330 --> 00:31:14,590
and brought this saxophone

767
00:31:14,590 --> 00:31:15,480
home for me.

768
00:31:16,270 --> 00:31:17,590
It was such a surprise.

769
00:31:21,330 --> 00:31:22,290
Your parents

770
00:31:23,550 --> 00:31:24,810
treat you really well.

771
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:25,830
They really do.

772
00:31:26,440 --> 00:31:27,700
When there's a chance,

773
00:31:27,850 --> 00:31:29,110
I'll take you to my home

774
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:29,830
for a meal.

775
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:37,610
My dad

776
00:31:38,380 --> 00:31:39,910
worked in transportation.

777
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:44,040
When I was in elementary school,

778
00:31:44,090 --> 00:31:45,700
my mom got pregnant again.

779
00:31:46,810 --> 00:31:47,830
To improve

780
00:31:47,830 --> 00:31:49,000
our family's life,

781
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:54,730
my dad worked overtime driving every day.

782
00:31:58,330 --> 00:31:59,350
He

783
00:31:59,420 --> 00:32:01,480
never spent the night out.

784
00:32:03,030 --> 00:32:04,460
But on his way back one night,

785
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:05,660
he had a car accident.

786
00:32:19,380 --> 00:32:21,040
To get from my home to Beijing,

787
00:32:21,530 --> 00:32:23,420
I have to take a bus for half an hour

788
00:32:23,420 --> 00:32:24,480
to the county town.

789
00:32:25,250 --> 00:32:26,740
Then I take a coach

790
00:32:26,740 --> 00:32:27,470
to Shanghai,

791
00:32:28,270 --> 00:32:30,500
and then take a train for over 10 hours

792
00:32:30,660 --> 00:32:32,120
to finally reach Beijing.

793
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:41,830
You know what?

794
00:32:42,830 --> 00:32:44,880
It took me 22 years

795
00:32:45,900 --> 00:32:47,330
to see the scenery

796
00:32:49,420 --> 00:32:51,000
that is just a summer

797
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:52,260
in your ordinary life.

798
00:33:39,750 --> 00:33:41,300
I called Director Ma

799
00:33:41,530 --> 00:33:42,660
and told him that

800
00:33:42,830 --> 00:33:45,270
the unopened bottle of liquor is authentic.

801
00:33:45,270 --> 00:33:46,590
What did Director Ma say?

802
00:33:46,590 --> 00:33:47,310
He said,

803
00:33:47,660 --> 00:33:49,000
let's just treat it as authentic.

804
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:51,480
But that bottle is authentic.

805
00:33:51,480 --> 00:33:52,680
Your words mean nothing.

806
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:54,680
It only works if Director Ma says it.

807
00:33:56,510 --> 00:33:57,190
Mr. Cui.

808
00:33:57,510 --> 00:33:59,240
I want to see Director Ma again.

809
00:33:59,570 --> 00:34:01,270
I want to explain it to him in person.

810
00:34:01,270 --> 00:34:02,840
Director Ma won't see you.

811
00:34:03,850 --> 00:34:04,910
Then what about...

812
00:34:05,460 --> 00:34:06,290
My role?

813
00:34:07,330 --> 00:34:08,170
Ranran,

814
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:09,940
there are plenty of roles.

815
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:11,380
Let's just wait.

816
00:34:11,380 --> 00:34:11,989
Okay?

817
00:34:15,530 --> 00:34:16,409
Mr. Cui.

818
00:34:16,780 --> 00:34:17,810
I'm begging you.

819
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:19,710
I have things to do.

820
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:20,699
I've got to go.

821
00:34:21,010 --> 00:34:21,880
Mr. Cui, I...

822
00:34:22,030 --> 00:34:22,960
I'm begging you.

823
00:34:23,070 --> 00:34:24,870
Just let me see Director Ma once.

824
00:34:24,940 --> 00:34:25,570
Just once.

825
00:34:25,570 --> 00:34:26,550
No, don't...

826
00:34:26,550 --> 00:34:27,210
Don't be like this.

827
00:34:27,210 --> 00:34:28,860
It looks bad if people see us like this.

828
00:34:28,860 --> 00:34:29,300
Look,

829
00:34:29,300 --> 00:34:31,630
Director Ma already said he won't see you.

830
00:34:32,380 --> 00:34:34,400
Then let me treat you to dinner, okay?

831
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:36,300
It's not about a meal.

832
00:34:36,300 --> 00:34:37,670
Then we'll do 2, 3, even 4 meals.

833
00:34:37,670 --> 00:34:38,880
Do you take me for a glutton?

834
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:40,380
Don't make this hard for me,

835
00:34:40,380 --> 00:34:41,130
okay?

836
00:34:45,320 --> 00:34:46,159
My money.

837
00:34:46,300 --> 00:34:47,150
Here, take this money.

838
00:34:47,150 --> 00:34:47,820
It's not much,

839
00:34:47,820 --> 00:34:48,480
but buy yourself some cigarettes.

840
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:49,380
Why are you buying me cigarettes?

841
00:34:49,380 --> 00:34:50,500
What kind of person do you think I am?

842
00:34:50,500 --> 00:34:51,070
Take it.

843
00:34:51,130 --> 00:34:52,659
What do you take me for? I...

844
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:53,780
I've never seen

845
00:34:53,780 --> 00:34:55,409
anyone as persistent as you.

846
00:34:56,380 --> 00:34:58,510
I really have no choice.

847
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:00,710
No, no, don't cry.

848
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:01,440
Don't cry.

849
00:35:01,630 --> 00:35:02,730
If someone I know sees us,

850
00:35:02,730 --> 00:35:04,210
they'd think I did something to you.

851
00:35:04,210 --> 00:35:04,570
I...

852
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:09,760
Ranran, really.

853
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:12,630
You must have been my mother in a past life.

854
00:35:12,630 --> 00:35:13,290
Seriously.

855
00:35:23,980 --> 00:35:25,380
Mr. Xu, is that a new bike?

856
00:35:26,860 --> 00:35:27,760
All the best with your business.

857
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:28,300
Thanks.

858
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:35,220
[Seasons Change Hotel]

859
00:35:34,530 --> 00:35:35,880
I was waiting inside for ages.

860
00:35:35,880 --> 00:35:36,840
And here you are.

861
00:35:39,650 --> 00:35:43,630
[Seasons Change Hotel]

862
00:35:40,050 --> 00:35:40,940
Where did you get this?

863
00:35:40,940 --> 00:35:41,880
I just bought it.

864
00:35:42,670 --> 00:35:43,620
You bought it?

865
00:35:44,570 --> 00:35:45,400
We can't keep borrowing a bike

866
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:46,550
from Little Northeasterner every day.

867
00:35:46,550 --> 00:35:47,410
Besides, look,

868
00:35:47,500 --> 00:35:48,830
I cleared the back seat.

869
00:35:49,590 --> 00:35:52,520
You don't have to squeeze
onto the bus every day, now.

870
00:35:54,070 --> 00:35:56,330
You spent the money as soon as you made it.

871
00:35:56,420 --> 00:35:58,020
Isn't this more convenient?

872
00:35:58,920 --> 00:35:59,450
Let's go.

873
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:00,530
Let's go.

874
00:36:00,940 --> 00:36:01,800
Then get on.

875
00:36:03,670 --> 00:36:04,130
Come on.

876
00:36:04,360 --> 00:36:05,150
Hold on tight.

877
00:36:05,150 --> 00:36:05,510
Okay.

878
00:36:05,780 --> 00:36:06,900
